article.headline: Arizona 96, Santa Barbara 80
article.story:
TUCSON, Ariz. (AP) -- Dee-Dee Wheeler scored 35 points and pulled
down 11 rebounds to pace Arizona to a 96-80 win over Cal-Santa
Barbara on Thursday night.

Natalie Jones added 23 points and eight assists while
Shawntinice Polk had 17 points for the Wildcats (7-2).

Cal-Santa Barbara (2-3) was led by Kristen Mann's 30 points
while Mia Fisher had 15 and Erin O'Bryan 14.

Wheeler made 13 field goals in 22 attempts including 7-of-11
from 3-point range.

Arizona shot 53 percent from the field in building a 46-36
halftime lead and coasted from there.
